elements.title: Diplobune
elements.contents: ... that the three-toed species of Diplobune (fossils pictured) were mammals of the order of "even-toed ungulates"?

elements.title: John F. Quirk
elements.contents: ... that as president of Loyola College in Maryland, John F. Quirk became close friends with the cardinal who ordained him a priest ten years earlier?

elements.title: elected team president
elements.contents: ... that contrary to NFL rules, the Green Bay Packers do not have a franchise owner and are instead led by an elected team president?

elements.title: Czesław Lewicki
elements.contents: ... that Czesław Lewicki, Polish composer and conductor, was recognized as Righteous Among the Nations for aiding the Polish-Jewish composer Władysław Szpilman?

elements.title: The Sims 2: Seasons
elements.contents: ... that PlantSims, human–plant hybrids in The Sims 2: Seasons, have been studied as examples of ecofeminism and deep ecology?

elements.title: Richard Worley
elements.contents: ... that Richard Worley played in minor baseball leagues and is now the commissioner of the Baltimore Police Department?

elements.title: temporary public holiday
elements.contents: ... that during a temporary public holiday to mourn the death of Elizabeth II, New Zealand had another public holiday on the same day?

elements.title: Michael Vinson
elements.contents: ... that Michael Vinson wasn't yet cheese, so he became milk instead?
